The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 01 March is 40,127 (4,644.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 24 February, there were 664 new confirmed cases (76.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 17 February, there were 763 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 13% (99 fewer cases).
